docs.abstract: Clayton Morris has been sued by nearly two dozen customers who say they were sold ramshackle homes as investment properties.

docs.lead_paragraph: INDIANAPOLIS — Clayton Morris walked away from his job as a Fox News host in 2017 to devote himself to the next phase of his professional life: helping regular people achieve financial independence.

headline.main: An Ex-Fox News Host Pitched ‘Financial Freedom.’ His Clients Want Their Money Back.
headline.print_headline: He Got Referral Fees. Clients Got Money Pits.

docs.abstract: A week after issuing a safety warning about the product, the company said it was taking all 4.7 million units off the market.
docs.snippet: A week after issuing a safety warning about the product, the company said it was taking all 4.7 million units off the market.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fisher-Price recalled all of its 4.7 million Rock ’n Play sleepers on Friday, days after a group of pediatricians urged its parent company, Mattel, to stop selling the product amid reports linking it to multiple infant deaths.

headline.main: Fisher-Price Recalls Rock ’n Play Sleeper Linked to Infant Deaths
headline.print_headline: Fisher-Price Recalls Sleeper After Reports Of Child Deaths

docs.abstract: The company knew for years about potential risks linked to its popular sleeper and about pediatricians’ objections to the way the product was being pitched to parents.
docs.snippet: The company knew for years about potential risks linked to its popular sleeper and about pediatricians’ objections to the way the product was being pitched to parents.
docs.lead_paragraph: The thousands of images of Fisher-Price’s Rock ’n Play sleeper posted on Instagram include many of babies snuggled serenely in the cloth-covered cradle, free of its harness and surrounded by blankets and stuffed animals.

headline.main: Before Fisher-Price’s Rock ’n Play Recall, Safety Fears and Dubious Marketing
headline.print_headline: Safety Fears Were Raised Before Sleeper Was Recalled

docs.abstract: The former auto executive, who is facing charges of financial wrongdoing in Japan, must await a court’s ruling on whether he will be released from prison.
docs.snippet: The former auto executive, who is facing charges of financial wrongdoing in Japan, must await a court’s ruling on whether he will be released from prison.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — A Tokyo court on Tuesday granted a request for bail by Carlos Ghosn, the former auto executive facing charges of financial wrongdoing in Japan, his lawyer’s office said, but added it would be “impossible” for him to be released the same day because of an appeal by the prosecutor’s office.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn, Former Nissan Chairman, Is Granted Bail Request in Japan

docs.abstract: Mr. Ghosn, the former head of the Nissan-Renault auto alliance, was formally charged with breach of trust, adding a new count of financial impropriety onto his existing three charges.
docs.snippet: Mr. Ghosn, the former head of the Nissan-Renault auto alliance, was formally charged with breach of trust, adding a new count of financial impropriety onto his existing three charges.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japanese prosecutors on Monday formally charged Carlos Ghosn, the former head of the Nissan-Renault auto alliance, with breach of trust, piling a new count of financial impropriety onto his existing charges in a move that adds pressure on him and ensures he remains jailed.

headline.main: Japanese Prosecutors Bring New Charge Against Carlos Ghosn
headline.print_headline: Japanese Prosecutors Bring a Fourth Charge Against Ghosn
